Technical Notes
Wastewater Viral Activity levels are based on the CDC methodology linked below, with two differences:
(1) use of weighted statistics (median and standard deviation) to calculate thresholds, with population served and reporting interval as weights; and
(2) The baseline is updated each time the WVA is calculated, rather than every 6 months.
The WVA is relative to the previous 12 months of data and is calculated independently for each panel. Because of this, WVA thresholds may be different across panels. The y-axis (copies/mL) is fixed, but the WVA levels are relative.
The trend line is a smoothed conditional mean, specifically a Locally Estimated Scatterplot Smoother (or LOESS).
All analysis and visualization is performed in R. Data and scripts are accessible in the github respository here: https://github.com/raughter/western-mass-covid.

Data Sources
CDC methodology: https://www.cdc.gov/nwss/about-data.html#data-method
Wastewater data access: https://www.mass.gov/info-details/wastewater-surveillance-reporting
Population weights are from various sources (EPA estimates whenever available).
